page.title: 01WRESTLINGWORTH TRANSPORT
page.content: Wrestlingworth is the eastern most parish in the county of Bedfordshire. It is the boundary between Bedfordshire and Cambridgeshire. Wreslingworth is on the B1042 road, five miles north-east of Biggleswade, sixteen miles east of Bedford and sixteen miles south-east of Cambridge. British Rail Eastern Region services run from Biggleswade and Sandy to Kings Cross and from Ashwell to Kings Cross on the Cambridge line. The A.1 trunk road lies six miles west of the village at Biggleswade. United Counties Omnibus Company run a service to Biggleswade and Cambridge but not to Potton or Sandy.
